This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine translation, which are typically covered under the arXiv category of Computer Science and Computation Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of embeddings, which are a popular technique in NLP and can be categorized under the subfield of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper's approach involves training models, which can be categorized under the subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of machine translation systems, which can be categorized under the subfield of Computer Vision (cs.CV) as it involves the use of language as a visual signal.
